column5: Three minutes of Aqua Vu underwater footage. Lots of bluegills and a few largies in there too.  I have seen numerous carp and muskie also, just didn't have the camera recording at the time.  Hope you enjoy!  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YSoPjPF1tXU
Thanks for the video! I spotted what I think to be smallies and rockbass. Which model is that Aqua View? I'm considering a new investment for ice fishing.
thanks for posting it I love watching underwater video  sometimes I forget to fish because I get too busy watching the fish with my cameras
73.2 F....I guess it will be awhile yet before she freezes over for the winter  Thx for the vid. Never tire of "Fish TV"
That was interesting...Thanks for posting...  There sure isn't a shortage of zebra mussels eh?  No wonder our lines get cut to ratsh!t...
I always enjoy watching underwater vids of fish in their environment... Thanks for posting!

Thanks for the positive feedback guys. I was using an Aqua Vu MAV unit, worked great all year.   I still can't believe how many fish I don't catch, but they are right beneath the boat. It can be frustrating at times, but hopefully with some more practice I'll get a few more hook-ups.  Cheers, Andrew
